-- Temelin Reactors Discussed by Czech, Russian Ministers, Lidove Noviny Says
-- B y   L a d k a   B a u e r o v a
-- 2010-09-24T05:14:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-24/temelin-reactors-discussed-by-czech-russian-ministers-lidove-noviny-says.html
Czech Foreign Minister Karel
Schwarzenberg met with his Russian counterpart Sergei Lavrov to
discuss the construction of two additional reactors at the
Temelin nuclear power plant, Lidove Noviny reported, citing
Schwarzenberg.  A Russian consortium led by ZAO Atomstroyexport is one of
the three bidders for the completion of Temelin. The two
ministers met on the sidelines of the United Nations general
meeting, the newspaper said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ladka Bauerova at 
 lbauerova@bloomberg.net  